  "created": "2026-03-21",
  "description": "The (3,4) spiral torus has pqScale=0.854 — below the default (2,3) at 0.933, meaning the coupling is more balanced than the default Torus. This produces a more even, four-strand interference pattern compared to the cinquefoil or default torus knots. macroKnot=0.3 tilts the matrix toward Figure-Eight, adding the alternating over/under crossing pattern to the spiral surface geometry. The result: a bright, articulate lead with a dense inner texture that shifts slightly with each note. Sine strands. Subtle vibrato LFO at 5.2 Hz. Play legato — glide reveals the spiral changing pitch.",
